<div id="content" class="subcolumns">
  <div class="main c75l">
    <div class="section">
    <div class="article">
      <h1>Flesh and divinity–pagans, Jews and Christians</h1>
        <div class="ct-meta-details">
        <ul class="cs-has-media">
  <li><a href="http://mpegmedia.abc.net.au/rn/podcast/2015/04/eot_20150402_1105.mp3" class="ico ico-audio" title="Download this item as MP3 (49.29MB)">Download audio</a></li>
    <li><a href="#" class="ico ico-text transcript-show">show transcript</a></li>
    </ul>
<dl>
          <dt>Broadcast:</dt>
<dd>Thursday 2 April 2015 11:05AM <a href="/radionational/programs/earshot/holy-thursday/6163894">(view full episode)</a></dd>
</dl>
      </div>
      <div class="section rich-text">
  <div class="inline-content photo full">
    <a href="/radionational/programs/earshot/velasco-image/6341076">











  
  
  
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  <img src="http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/image/6341076-3x2-700x467.jpg" alt="Hapag ng Pag-asa, “table of hope,”  by Filipino artist, Joey Velasco (1967-2010)." title="Hapag ng Pag-asa, “table of hope,”  by Filipino artist, Joey Velasco (1967-2010)." />
</a><a href="/radionational/programs/earshot/velasco-image/6341076"><strong>Image:</strong>
       <em>Hapag ng Pag-asa ('</em>table of hope') by  by Filipino artist, Joey Velasco (1967-2010). <span class="source">(With permission)</span>
      </a></div><p> </p><p>Are Christians pagan?  Some strands in Jewish thought say that Christians are at least tempted towards paganism.  Did ‘the Jews’ kill Jesus? This 'Holy Week' when Christians listen to John’s Gospel as they follow the Passion of Jesus Christ, that’s what they hear. These ideas are the grit of Jewish Christian discussion.</p><p>We spoke to <a class="external" href="http://divinity.vanderbilt.edu/people/bio/amy-jill-levine">Amy-Jill (A-J) Levine, university professor of New Testament and Jewish Studies at Vanderbilt in Nashville, Tennessee</a>. She is the co-editor with <a class="external" href="http://people.brandeis.edu/~brettler/">Marc Zvi Brettler</a> of <a class="external" href="https://global.oup.com/academic/product/the-jewish-annotated-new-testament-9780195297706?cc=au&amp;lang=en&amp;">The Jewish Annotated New Testament</a>, OUP, New York, 2011. We also spoke to Francis J. (Frank) Moloney, an extensively published biblical scholar whose forthcoming book <a class="external" href="http://www.garrattpublishing.com.au/product/9781925009804/"><em>Body Broken for a Broken People: Divorce, Remarriage and the Eucharist</em></a> is timed to enter an important debate at the Vatican about Catholic teaching on marriage and divorce. He is currently leading the Biblical and Early Christian Studies team at the <a class="external" href="http://www.acu.edu.au/about_acu/faculties,_institutes_and_centres/theology_and_philosophy/institute_for_religion_and_critical_inquiry/biblical_and_early_christian_studies">Australian Catholic University’s Institute for Religion and Critical Inquiry</a>.</p><p>Poet and memoirist <a class="external" href="http://www.poetryfoundation.org/bio/mary-karr">Mary Karr</a> reads her poem <em>Disgraced</em>. Born in 1955 and raised in Texas, she is the author of several critically acclaimed books of poetry, including <em>Abacus </em>(1987; reprinted 2007), <em>The Devil’s Tour</em>(1993), <em>Viper Rum </em>(2001), and <em>Sinners Welcome </em>(2006). She is also the author of a trilogy of memoirs <em>The Liar’s Club </em>(1995), <em>Cherry</em> (2001), and <em>Lit </em>(2009). <a class="external" href="https://www.dur.ac.uk/theology.religion/staff/profile/?id=12513">Professor Karen Kilby, Bede Professor of Catholic Theology at the University of Durham</a> finds useful a critical contemporary Jewish philosophical angle on Christianity, and Fred Morgan, the <a class="external" href="http://www.tbi.org.au/about/our-rabbis/">Emeritus Rabbi of the Temple Beth Israel</a> in Melbourne's St Kilda describes a new ‘grassroots dialogue’ venture. He is committed to interfaith dialogue and has long been involved in the Victorian Council of Christians and Jews, serving as its President.  Read Rabbi Morgan's remarks on <a class="external" href="http://www.assembly.uca.org.au/rof/images/stories/resources/papersandstatements/rabbimorganpursuing.pdf" target="_blank" title="Rabbi Fred Morgan on Interfaith Dialogue">Pursuing Interfaith Dialogue: From Security to Redemption</a>,  delivered to the Council of Christians and Jews (Vic).</p><p><a class="external" href="http://www.trinity.unimelb.edu.au/people/staff-directory/dorothy-lee.html">Dorothy Lee,</a> a biblical scholar, specialising in Johannine studies, who is Professor in New Testament and Dean of <a class="external" href="http://www.trinity.unimelb.edu.au/learning/theological-school.html">Trinity Theological School</a> within the <a class="external" href="http://www.divinity.edu.au/">University of Divinity</a>, Bracha Rafael, a volunteer in a Grassroots Dialogue Initiative sponsored by the Victorian Council of Christians and Jews and Steve Sutton, her fellow volunteer and a pastor at the <a class="external" href="http://www.fitzroynorthchurch.org.au/">North Fitzroy Community Church</a> in Melbourne also feature.</p><p>Thanks to <a class="external" href="http://www.poetryfoundation.org/foundation/about">The Poetry Foundation</a> for permission to broadcast Mary Karr's reading of her poem. Mary Karr discusses her poem <a class="external" href="http://www.poetryfoundation.org/features/audioitem/3888">here</a>.</p><p><em>Hapag ng Pag-asa,</em> 'table of hope,' is the work of Filipino artist <a class="external" href="http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/lifestyle/07/20/10/heartist-painter-velasco-passes-away">Joey Velasco</a> (1967-2010). His work situated Jesus Christ among the Filipino poor, to awake a sense of faith, and is a cry to social action for the underprivileged. It is reproduced with the permission of the artist’s widow, Queeny Velasco, and the <a class="external" href="http://roelc07.com/portfolio/the-joey-velasco-foundation/" target="_blank" title="">Joey Velasco Foundation, Inc</a>.  Francis J. Moloney chose this image for the front cover of his forthcoming <a class="external" href="http://www.garrattpublishing.com.au/product/9781925009804/" target="_blank" title="">book</a>.</p></div>
