	<h3>Suzanne Dixon :</h3>
	<p class="date">02 Apr 2015 1:04:09pm</p>
	<p class="comment">This was interesting and I shall be following up some of the reading, particularly the Jewish-annotated NT.<br />My familiarity with classical and Hellenistic sources has made me very conscious of the strong rhetorical and philosophical borrowings in the NT (not a novel observation, I know) and I've always been curious about the extent to which the early church was influenced by Jewish tradition. <br /><br />The use of 'Christian&quot; to mean specifically western (Roman) catholic bemused me. It soon became apparent that that was the whole position of the broadcast, but I'm puzzled about why that was not made explicit.</p>
	
	<p class="links">
