	<h3>Amanda :</h3>
	<p class="date">02 Apr 2015 3:50:37pm</p>
	<p class="comment">I'm not sure that I agree that Christians - at least, they shouldn’t hear it – hear: &quot;Did ‘the Jews’ kill Jesus? This 'Holy Week' when Christians listen to John’s Gospel as they follow the Passion of Jesus Christ, that’s what they hear.&quot;<br /><br />What we can do is point the finger at Jesus himself - it was his choice to die. No one forced him. His entire reason for existing as a human was to die.<br /><br />In my experience growing up in a Christian household, with missionary parents, preacher grandfathers and going to a Christian school full of Bible studies for most of my schooling, I never once heard anyone blame the people living in Israel at that time for Jesus' death and neither did anyone else I know who still follows Christianity.  <br /><br />Although I'd love to hear from anyone in the comments here if they WERE taught that! <br /><br />Fundamentalist religiosity may have played a part but you can find that in any religion, cult and belief system – all human beings will stuff up, mis-interpret their religious texts, live hypocritically and so on. Also, remember that &quot;Whoever here is without sin can be the first to throw a stone at her.&quot; The meaning of this is that if you’re perfect, then you can judge others. None of us are perfect, therefore none of us should judge anyone else - least of all Christians for whom this message is intended.</p>
	
	<p class="links">
	    <a href="http://www2b.abc.net.au/tmb/View/NewMessage.aspx?b=335&amp;t=57&amp;tn=&amp;dm=1&amp;m=362&amp;tpa=&amp;r=%2ftmb%2fView%2fMessage.aspx%3fb%3d335%26t%3d57%26a%3d0%26ps%3d50%26tpa%3d%26uto%3d1%26dm%3d4%26ci%3d0%26pd%3d1%26so%3dDateTime%26soa%3dTrue%26p%3d1%26p2%3d0">Reply</a>
	    
