<li class="">
	<a id="m_ucMessageDisplay412_m_anchMessageAnchor" name="m412"></a>
	<h3>Rodney Wetherell :</h3>
	<p class="date">06 Apr 2015 10:44:35pm</p>
	<p class="comment">Thank you for this excellent program, presenting so many points of view on aspects of St John's Gospel which cast 'the Jews' in a  bad light - when nearly all those present in the events leading up to the Crucifixion, apart from a few Romans, were Jews, including Jesus and his disciples. This has bothered me over the years, and I was glad to hear various comments on it. A greater understanding of Jesus' place within Judaism would no doubt have lessened anti-Semitism over many centuries. Yet I feel we are not all that enlightened now - and anti-Semitism is again on the rise in Europe.</p>
	
	<p class="links">
	    <a href="http://www2b.abc.net.au/tmb/View/NewMessage.aspx?b=335&amp;t=57&amp;tn=&amp;dm=1&amp;m=412&amp;tpa=&amp;r=%2ftmb%2fView%2fMessage.aspx%3fb%3d335%26t%3d57%26a%3d0%26ps%3d50%26tpa%3d%26uto%3d1%26dm%3d4%26ci%3d0%26pd%3d1%26so%3dDateTime%26soa%3dTrue%26p%3d1%26p2%3d0">Reply</a>
	    
